286
00:24:39,300 --> 00:24:44,300
meaning equations that describe how things change from moment to moment or place to place,

287
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:48,300
little differences in time or space, hence differential.

288
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:58,300
He wrote differential equations that encoded what Faraday and Ersted and Gauss and Ampere had discovered.

289
00:24:58,300 --> 00:25:03,300
So now these physical discoveries from science, from tinkering,

290
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:08,300
were put in the language of math, and then comes the spooky part.

291
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:12,300
I mean it may not surprise you that math can describe physical phenomena.

292
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:16,300
We know that math is a language, but math is much more than a language,

293
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:21,300
and this is the part that I find uncanny, and that I think has something to do with what Feynman was talking about,

294
00:25:21,300 --> 00:25:25,300
that with math you can actually manipulate equations.

295
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:31,300
You know that you can add and subtract if you're doing stuff with numbers,

296
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:36,300
but in algebra you do things like substitute a variable into another equation,

297
00:25:36,300 --> 00:25:41,300
or you can divide, or in calculus you can do similar things, but they're more sophisticated,

298
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:46,300
and these manipulations, I want you to think of the word manipulate like in the spas here in town,

299
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:49,300
where you have a masseuse who's actually manipulating you,

300
00:25:49,300 --> 00:25:52,300
and maybe you start mumbling and telling some intimate secrets.

