00:29:52,300 --> 00:29:55,300
It's not just playing games with symbols.

351
00:29:55,300 --> 00:30:03,300
Nature is somehow doing the same thing that, I mean I find this really bizarre, so do many other people,

352
00:30:03,300 --> 00:30:12,300
that we, with our puny primate logic, happen to have stumbled across something that mirrors the way nature really works,

353
00:30:12,300 --> 00:30:19,300
that you can predict stuff that is out there, and then by learning to speak this strange language,

354
00:30:19,300 --> 00:30:26,300
and by discovering that it taps into nature's hidden logic, we can use calculus to remake the world.

355
00:30:26,300 --> 00:30:32,300
So that's the gist of the argument here, this is why calculus matters, at least from one point of view.

356
00:30:32,300 --> 00:30:39,300
Now, in telling the story of calculus, I want to, at this moment, personify calculus.

